<span id="Description"></span>
== Descripción == 

La herramienta [[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface.svg|24px]] [[Surface_GeomFillSurface|Superficie de Relleno Geométrico]] crea una superficie paramétrica a partir de dos, tres o cuatro bordes de contorno, tratando de crear una transición suave entre ellos.

[[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface_4_edges.png|330px]] [[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface_4_edges_example.png|330px]]

[[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface_3_edges.png|330px]] [[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface_3_edges_example.png|330px]]

[[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface_2_edges.png|330px]] [[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface_2_edges_example.png|330px]]

{{Leyenda|Izquierda: Aristas que se utilizan para generar una superficie con la herramienta [[Surface_GeomFillSurface|Relleno Geométrico de Superficie]], 4 aristas conectadas, 3 aristas conectadas y 2 aristas desconectadas. Derecha: superficie resultante del uso de 4, 3 y 2 aristas, respectivamente.}}

<span id="Usage"></span>
== Uso ==

# Existen varias formas de usar la herramienta:
#* Pulse el botón {{Button|[[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface.svg|16px]] [[Surface_GeomFillSurface|Rellenar Curvas de Contorno]]}}.

#* Seleccione la opción {{MenuCommand|Superficie → [[Image:Surface_GeomFillSurface.svg|16px]] Rellenar Curvas de Contorno}} del menú.

# Seleccione los bordes en la [[3D_view|Vista 3D]]. Los bordes deben estar conectados y formar un contorno cerrado.

# Pulse {{Button|Aceptar}}.

{{Emphasis|Nota:}} Una vez creada, no es posible aplicar restricciones adicionales a la superficie creada.

<span id="Options"></span>
== Opciones ==

{{MenuCommand|Tipo de Relleno}}: {{RadioButton|TRUE|Estirada}}, {{RadioButton|TRUE|Coons}}, or {{RadioButton|TRUE|Curvada}}.

<span id="Properties"></span>
== Propiedades ==

Un objeto [[Surface_GeomFillSurface|Surface GeomFillSurface]] (clase {{incode|Surface::GeomFillSurface}}) se deriva de la [[Part_Feature|Part Feature]] básica (clase {{incode|Part::Feature}}, a través de la subclase {{incode|Part::Spline}}), por lo tanto, comparte todas las propiedades de esta última.

Además de las propiedades descritas en [[Part_Feature|Características de Pieza]], el objeto Surface GeomFillSurface tiene las siguientes propiedades en la [[Property_View|Vista de Propiedades]].

<span id="Data"></span>
=== Datos ===

{{TitleProperty|Base}}

*{{PropertyData|Tipo de Relleno|Enumeración}}: El algoritmo de relleno aplicado; Estirado, el estilo con los parches más planos; [https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Coons_patch {{Value|Coons}}], un estilo redondeado con menos profundidad que Curvado; Curvado, el estilo con los parches más redondeados.

*{{PropertyData|Boundary List|LinkSubList}}: una lista de aristas que se utilizarán para construir la superficie.

*{{PropertyData|Reversed List|BoolList|(hidden)}}:

<span id="View"></span>
=== Vistas ===

{{TitleProperty|Base}}

* {{PropertyView|Control Points|Bool}}: it defaults to {{FALSE}}; if set to {{TRUE}}, it will show an overlay with the control points of the surface.

== Twisting of the surface ==

The shape of the surface depends on the direction of the chosen edges; if edges are selected and the result is a surface that "twists" on itself, one of the edges may need its list of vertices in the reverse order. A surface that twists on itself will probably have self-intersections, and thus will be an invalid [[Part_TopoShape|Shape]]; this can be verified with [[File:Part_CheckGeometry.svg|16px]] [[Part_CheckGeometry|Part CheckGeometry]].

For example, if two curves have the points
{{Code|code=
curve1 = [a, b, c, d]
curve2 = [e, f, g]
}}
and the resulting surface after using [[File:Surface_GeomFillSurface.svg|16px]] [[Surface_GeomFillSurface|Surface GeomFillSurface]] or [[File:Surface_Sections.svg|16px]] [[Surface_Sections|Surface Sections]] is a twisted surface, you may create a third curve that is equal to one of the two original curves but with a reversed list of points.

Either
{{Code|code=
curve1 = [a, b, c, d]
curve3 = [g, f, e]
}}

or
{{Code|code=
curve3 = [d, c, b, a]
curve2 = [e, f, g]
}}
should work to generate a surface that doesn't twist.

In practical terms this means that all edges used to generate a surface should be created preferably in the same clockwise or anti-clockwise direction. Following this simple rule usually guarantees that the surface will follow the smoothest direction and won't twist.

When the surface's {{PropertyView|Lighting}} property is {{Value|One side}}, a face will be painted completely black if its normal direction points into the [[3D_View|3D View]] (away from the current viewer), indicating a flipped face with respect to the other colored faces.

[[File:Surface_twisting_example_smooth.png|330px]] [[File:Surface_twisting_example_twisted.png|330px]]
{{Caption|Left: the boundary edges are oriented in the same direction, and thus the generated surface is smooth. Right: the boundary edges have opposite directions, and thus the generated surface twists on itself, resulting in self-intersections.}}

== Scripting ==

See also: [[FreeCAD_Scripting_Basics|FreeCAD Scripting Basics]].

The Surface GeomFillSurface tool can be used in [[Macros|macros]] and from the [[Python_Console|Python Console]] by adding the {{incode|Surface::GeomFillSurface}} object.
* The edges to be used to define the surface must be assigned as a [[FeaturePython_Custom_Properties#App::PropertyLinkSubList|LinkSubList]] to the {{incode|BoundaryList}} property of the object.
* The type of algorithm must be assigned like a string to the {{incode|FillType}} property.
* All objects with edges need to be computed before they can be used as input for the properties of the GeomFillSurface object.

{{Code|code=
import FreeCAD as App
import Draft

doc = App.newDocument()

a = App.Vector(-140, -100, 0)
b = App.Vector(175, -108, 0)
c = App.Vector(200, 101, 0)
d = App.Vector(-135, 107, 70)

points1 = [a, App.Vector(-55, -91, 65), App.Vector(35, -85, -5), b]
obj1 = Draft.make_bspline(points1)

points2 = [b, App.Vector(217, -45, 55), App.Vector(217, 35, -15), c]
obj2 = Draft.make_bspline(points2)

points3 = [c, App.Vector(33, 121, 55), App.Vector(0, 91, 15), App.Vector(-80, 121, -40), d]
obj3 = Draft.make_bspline(points3)

points4 = [d, App.Vector(-140, 0, 45), a]
obj4 = Draft.make_bspline(points4)
doc.recompute()

surf = doc.addObject("Surface::GeomFillSurface", "Surface")
surf.BoundaryList = [(obj1, "Edge1"),
                     (obj2, "Edge1"),
                     (obj3, "Edge1"),
                     (obj4, "Edge1")]
doc.recompute()
}}


